The magnitude of resultant vector $R^{\prime}=\sqrt{a^{2}+b^{2}+2 a b \cos \theta}$

Here $\mathrm{a}=\mathrm{b}=\mathrm{R}$
Then $\mathrm{R}^{\prime}=\sqrt{\mathrm{R}^{2}+\mathrm{R}^{2}+2 \mathrm{R}^{2} \cos \theta}$

$$
\begin{aligned}
& =R \sqrt{2} \sqrt{1+\cos \theta} \\
& =\sqrt{2} R \sqrt{2 \cos ^{2} \frac{\theta}{2}} \\
& =2 R \cos \frac{\theta}{2}
\end{aligned}
$$
